特别策划

铁路数据服务平台安全策略研究 武威 等

Research on Safety Strategy of Railway Data Service Platform
WU Wei，MA Xiaoning，LIU Yanjun，ZHANG Xiaodong （Railway Big Data Research & Application Innovation Center，China Academy of
Railway Sciences Corporation Limited，Beijing 100081，China）
Abstract：As the IT application of railway is constantly improving, the information systems have accumulated massive data. The establishment of railway data service platform implements the one-stop data processing procedure including acquisition, processing, storage, sharing, analysis and visualization of massive data. Being the big data platform for centralized storage and management of railway massive data, the railway data service platform confronts safety risks in different aspects such as basic environment, data management, platform management, etc. Data safety assurance is a key issue to be considered. Through analysis of safety threats faced by the platform, the paper designed the safety structure and worked out the corresponding safety strategy, implementing the safety management control of platform and ensuring the safety of platform data. Keywords：railway data service platform；safety risk；safety structure；safety strategy；big data

（上接第 62 页）
Application of Text Big Data Analysis Technique in the Field of Railway Train Operation Safety
YANG Lianbao，LI Ping，LIU Yifei （Institute of Computing Technology，China Academy of Railway Sciences Corporation Limited，Beijing 100081，China）
Abstract：Guaranteeing train operation safety is the priority for railway department. It is one of major approaches for improving train operation safety to analyze accident cause through such text data as railway accident investigation report. Considering that railway system has enormous non-construction accident and failure text data which are difficult to be searched and analyzed, the paper puts forward the general framework of text data analysis of railway train operation safety, including the whole process from text data integration, storage, processing, calculating, searching, analysis to application. The paper also carries out a research based on railway text data analysis technique such as full-text search and feature extraction. In conclusion, the paper takes the accident investigation report of a CR branch company as a sample and implements full-text search, cloud display of failure words and correlation analysis of it, obtaining a good result. Keywords：big data；non-construction；train operation safety；accident and failure；full-text search；text mining

